<!--
  ================================================================
  SITEMAP — Hammad Khan Portfolio
  ================================================================

  HOW TO USE THIS SITEMAP:

  STEP 1 — Replace the domain
    Find every instance of: https://www.hammadkhan.com
    Replace with YOUR actual live URL, for example:
      • https://yourusername.github.io/portfolio
      • https://yourname.netlify.app
      • https://hammadkhan.pk  (if you have a custom domain)

  STEP 2 — Upload sitemap.xml to your website root
    The file must be accessible at:
      https://yourdomain.com/sitemap.xml
    On GitHub Pages: place sitemap.xml in the root of your repo
    On Netlify: place sitemap.xml alongside index.html

  STEP 3 — Submit to Google Search Console
    • Go to https://search.google.com/search-console
    • Add your website property (if not already added)
    • Left sidebar → Sitemaps
    • Enter: sitemap.xml
    • Click Submit

  STEP 4 — Also submit to Bing (optional but recommended)
    • Go to https://www.bing.com/webmasters
    • Add your site → Sitemaps → Submit sitemap.xml

  NOTE: This is a single-page application (SPA). The sitemap
  lists the main page + all anchor sections as separate URLs
  so Google indexes each section of your portfolio individually.
  ================================================================
-->
